  "notes": "Test data generation assumptions and methodology:\n\n1. **Physical Realism**: All values respect physical constraints:\n   - LAI/SAI >= 0 (leaf/stem area index)\n   - coszen in [-1, 1] (cosine of solar zenith angle)\n   - Soil moisture (h2osoi) in [0, 1] as volumetric fraction\n   - watsat (saturation) in [0, 1]\n   - dz (layer thickness) > 0\n   - denh2o = 1000 kg/m3 (standard water density)\n\n2. **Soil Layer Structure**:\n   - CLM4.5: 15 ground layers (nlevgrnd=15)\n   - CLM5.0: 20 soil layers (nlevsoi=20)\n   - Layer thickness increases with depth (typical CLM profile)\n   - nbedrock indicates impermeable layer depth\n\n3. **Test Coverage**:\n   - Nominal (5 cases): Typical growing season, multiple configurations\n   - Edge (3 cases): Zero LAI/SAI, night-time, drought, saturation\n   - Special (2 cases): Shallow bedrock, dense canopy, sunrise, heterogeneous\n\n4. **Dimension Consistency**:\n   - Each test maintains consistent array dimensions\n   - n_patches can differ from n_columns (multiple patches per column)\n   - All soil arrays shaped [n_columns, nlevgrnd]\n\n5. **CLM Version Testing**:\n   - Mixed CLM4.5 and CLM5.0 tests\n   - Both versions use same input structure but different soil layer counts\n\n6. **Soil Moisture Profiles**:\n   - Generally increase with depth (gravitational drainage)\n   - Respect watsat constraints (cannot exceed saturation)\n   - Range from very dry (0.01) to saturated conditions\n\n7. **Solar Geometry**:\n   - coszen = 1.0: sun directly overhead\n   - coszen = 0.0: sunrise/sunset\n   - coszen < 0: night-time (sun below horizon)\n   - Values chosen to cover full diurnal cycle\n\n8. **Vegetation States**:\n   - LAI ranges: 0 (bare) to 8.5 (dense tropical forest)\n   - SAI typically 20-30% of LAI\n   - Zero values test bare soil/winter conditions\n\n9. **Array Generation**:\n   - Nested lists represent multi-dimensional arrays\n   - Can be directly converted to JAX/NumPy arrays\n   - All indices are 0-based (Python convention)\n\n10. **Edge Case Rationale**:\n    - Zero LAI/SAI: Tests bare soil radiation/energy balance\n    - Negative coszen: Tests night-time code paths\n    - Minimal moisture: Tests drought stress conditions\n    - Saturated soil: Tests drainage/runoff limits\n    - Shallow bedrock: Tests restricted root zone\n    - High LAI: Tests dense canopy light attenuation"
